WEBVTT

00:06.381 --> 00:08.089
SAM: <i>My son was murdered</i>
<i>near here.</i>

00:08.589 --> 00:11.547
<i>There was this time after,</i>
<i>I'd suddenly be convinced</i>

00:11.631 --> 00:13.172
<i>that everyone was lying.</i>

00:13.547 --> 00:15.673
<i>Episodic psychosis they call it.</i>

00:16.088 --> 00:18.714
-That is just grief.
-Is it?

00:19.422 --> 00:20.464
SAM: <i>Because I don't know.</i>

00:20.547 --> 00:22.506
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

00:22.589 --> 00:24.506
-(INDISTINCT CLAMORING)
-SAM: <i>What is it these people</i>
<i>believe?</i>

00:24.589 --> 00:27.964
JESS: <i>The ancient Celts</i>
<i>believed Osea was the soul</i>
<i>of the world.</i>

00:28.589 --> 00:30.923
You wanna know more about it,
you should talk to Mimir.

00:31.005 --> 00:32.464
SAM: <i>Mimir? You said Mimir?</i>

00:33.214 --> 00:34.589
JESS: <i>Wait, why?</i>
<i>Do you know him?</i>

00:35.923 --> 00:37.089
Why do you have this?

00:37.923 --> 00:39.130
Did you see my son?

00:39.631 --> 00:41.089
What did we do to you?

00:41.923 --> 00:43.673
SAM: He was looking into
my son's death,

00:43.756 --> 00:45.172
and Epona's trying to hang
herself

00:45.255 --> 00:47.756
<i>in the exact spot where Nathan</i>
<i>was found.</i>

00:47.839 --> 00:48.964
<i>They're connected.</i>

00:49.047 --> 00:50.255
Sam, you need to come with us.

00:50.339 --> 00:51.881
<i>He wants you dead</i>
<i>and he means it.</i>

00:51.964 --> 00:53.381
We need to get you away
from here.

00:53.464 --> 00:55.005
♪ (MUSIC FADES) ♪

00:55.089 --> 00:57.631
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

01:03.422 --> 01:04.964
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

01:30.422 --> 01:33.255
(bell ringing)

01:33.339 --> 01:35.214
Preacher:
Take these things in Your name.

01:35.297 --> 01:37.172
-Take this man in Your name.
-(panting)

01:37.255 --> 01:39.422
-(gasps)
-(preacher continues,
indistinct)

01:39.506 --> 01:40.964
(match strikes)

01:41.047 --> 01:41.923
(flame roars)

01:42.005 --> 01:44.339
♪

01:44.422 --> 01:46.506
-(flames burst)
-(whispering, bell ringing)

01:46.589 --> 01:48.589
(flame roars)

01:48.673 --> 01:50.881
-(whispering continues)
-(screams)

01:51.756 --> 01:52.631
(gasps)

01:52.714 --> 01:56.255
(overlapping murmuring)

01:56.339 --> 01:58.798
-(baby crying)
-Shh...

01:58.881 --> 02:02.255
Baby, baby, baby, no!
No, no, no, no!

02:02.339 --> 02:05.589
(woman speaking gibberish)

02:05.673 --> 02:07.506
(muffled chatter)

02:07.589 --> 02:09.547
(baby screeches)

02:09.631 --> 02:11.923
(indistinct chattering)

02:12.005 --> 02:13.631
Larry:
He is tripping hard.

02:13.714 --> 02:15.881
-Whoa! (laughs)
-(Sam laughing)

02:15.964 --> 02:17.339
(giggles)

02:17.422 --> 02:20.130
(scuttling)

02:20.214 --> 02:21.798
-Oh...
-(whispering)

02:21.881 --> 02:24.422
Preacher (whispering):
Oh Lord, give Osea
the Father it needs.

02:24.506 --> 02:28.214
Bring us the true Father.
Give us the true Father...

02:29.547 --> 02:31.089
(child giggling)

02:31.172 --> 02:32.589
(gasps)

02:32.673 --> 02:34.547
(rattling)

02:35.839 --> 02:39.089
(scuttling)

02:39.172 --> 02:42.255
-Join me... with him.
-(groaning)

02:42.339 --> 02:44.839
And let
this put the blood

02:44.923 --> 02:47.673
-of the land that has
redeemed him inside him.
-(groaning, struggling)

02:47.756 --> 02:50.798
-(heavy breathing)
-And on this bread...

02:50.881 --> 02:53.339
(continues, indistinct)

02:53.422 --> 02:54.964
(beating)

02:55.047 --> 02:58.047
-(struggling, grimacing)
-(squishing)

02:58.130 --> 03:01.422
(tense music playing)

03:04.297 --> 03:05.422
Oh!

03:06.964 --> 03:09.714
(disgusted grunt, gasping)

03:12.798 --> 03:14.631
Does anyone else
know you took him?

03:14.714 --> 03:17.422
-(scuttling)
-Of course they fucking don't.

03:17.506 --> 03:20.673
-That's why we need
to end him, now.
-(groans, gasps)

03:20.756 --> 03:22.464
No.

03:22.547 --> 03:24.047
We're going
a different way.

03:24.130 --> 03:25.297
-(baby crying)
-(gasps)

03:25.381 --> 03:28.506
-(flapping)
-Larry: What'd I bring
him here for then?

03:28.589 --> 03:29.839
(gasps)

03:29.923 --> 03:32.255
What the fuck are you
gonna do with him?

03:32.339 --> 03:34.589
Save him!

03:35.756 --> 03:36.881
(exhales)

03:36.964 --> 03:39.631
We're going to save him.

03:41.756 --> 03:44.422
(shallow breathing)

03:47.673 --> 03:51.381
-(shallow breathing)
-(door opens)

03:51.464 --> 03:53.631
Father:
Take him downstairs.

03:54.798 --> 03:56.464
Keep him safe!

03:56.547 --> 03:59.547
Larry:
Safe, eh? We'll see.

03:59.631 --> 04:01.881
(ragged breathing)

04:01.964 --> 04:02.923
(chuckles)

04:05.839 --> 04:09.339
-(chair creaking)
-(Sam groaning)

04:09.422 --> 04:10.381
-(thud)
-(gasps)

04:10.464 --> 04:12.422
(scraping)

04:12.506 --> 04:15.839
(nervous panting)

04:15.964 --> 04:18.255
(laughing)

04:18.339 --> 04:21.005
(thudding grunting)

04:21.089 --> 04:22.547
(Larry humming)

04:22.631 --> 04:24.798
-(grunting)
-(laughs)

04:24.881 --> 04:27.506
(bang, creaking)

04:28.673 --> 04:30.005
Ah!

04:41.798 --> 04:44.964
(shallow breathing)

04:47.172 --> 04:50.464
-(doors slamming)
-(indistinct chatter)

04:53.964 --> 04:55.047
(slams door)

05:00.214 --> 05:01.422
(snapping)

05:04.214 --> 05:06.339
(man groans)

05:11.381 --> 05:13.547
Sam:
Mimir?

05:13.631 --> 05:16.547
-Can you help me?
-(bottle rolling)

05:17.589 --> 05:20.714
(light snapping)

05:23.881 --> 05:27.089
-(heart beating)
-(indistinct whispering)

05:28.673 --> 05:30.005
(chokes)

05:32.714 --> 05:34.881
(gasping)

05:34.964 --> 05:37.589
(lights buzzing)

05:39.839 --> 05:41.255
(sighs)

05:44.089 --> 05:46.756
-Where am I?
-In the Big House.

05:53.005 --> 05:55.339
They fucking did things to me.

05:55.422 --> 05:57.005
Like...

05:57.089 --> 05:59.339
Like a ceremony.
They put blood and wine on me.

05:59.422 --> 06:03.089
You were baptized
in Esus' name.

06:03.923 --> 06:05.881
What are you talking about?

06:05.964 --> 06:09.923
The Celts believed Osea
was the soul of the world.

06:10.005 --> 06:14.547
It needed a father to
shepherd it through the dark.

06:14.631 --> 06:16.756
Charrington was that father,

06:16.839 --> 06:18.214
then his son was.

06:18.297 --> 06:20.923
But his son decided
he didn't want this life

06:21.005 --> 06:23.130
for his own boy,
and they fled.

06:23.214 --> 06:24.756
Why are you telling me all this?

06:24.839 --> 06:26.964
His brother took over.

06:27.047 --> 06:29.089
But as the brother
comes closer to death,

06:29.172 --> 06:30.297
with no male heir,

06:30.381 --> 06:33.214
the island declines,
and so does the world.

06:33.297 --> 06:35.798
What the fuck does all this
got to do with me?

06:35.881 --> 06:38.005
(light buzzing)

06:38.547 --> 06:39.839
Your grandfather

06:39.923 --> 06:43.005
told you he was
stationed on Osea,

06:43.089 --> 06:44.673
yes?

06:45.464 --> 06:46.964
He was not.

06:47.047 --> 06:48.714
He was born here.

06:48.798 --> 06:51.589
He was the son of
the son of Charrington.

06:52.130 --> 06:54.589
The father who fled.

06:54.673 --> 06:55.798
(gasps)

06:55.881 --> 06:58.339
He didn't want this for his son,

06:58.422 --> 07:00.756
and they did not
want it for you.

07:00.839 --> 07:03.422
♪

07:03.506 --> 07:07.172
You are the rightful
father of Osea, Sam.

07:10.673 --> 07:12.839
Can you feel it coming?

07:13.923 --> 07:15.214
The darkness.

07:15.297 --> 07:18.172
-(door opens)
-Who the fuck put
you in here, eh?!

07:18.255 --> 07:20.714
Mimir:
I-- I was left here.

07:20.798 --> 07:22.964
I said nothing to him!

07:29.506 --> 07:32.714
-(squishing)
-(groaning, screaming)

07:34.964 --> 07:37.839
-Shh...
-(muffled groaning)

07:39.255 --> 07:40.297
(tape stretching)

07:40.381 --> 07:43.005
They may wanna save you,
but I fucking don't.

07:46.130 --> 07:48.214
(muffled groan)

07:54.422 --> 07:56.297
(indistinct whispering)

07:56.381 --> 07:58.464
-(muffled yelling)
-(Larry shushing)

07:58.547 --> 08:00.297
(chatter continues)

08:00.381 --> 08:01.964
-(muffled groaning)
-Larry (whispers): Shit.

08:02.047 --> 08:05.089
♪

08:06.005 --> 08:08.172
(heavy breathing)

08:09.714 --> 08:12.839
(lock beeping)

08:17.964 --> 08:21.089
(heavy breathing)

08:22.506 --> 08:24.673
(birds squawking)

08:26.255 --> 08:29.464
(waves washing ashore)

08:31.047 --> 08:33.047
(dramatic music playing)

08:33.130 --> 08:35.255
♪

08:42.964 --> 08:45.089
(wind blowing)

08:56.631 --> 08:59.756
(indistinct yelling)

09:02.506 --> 09:05.005
(muffled yelling)

09:05.089 --> 09:08.255
♪

09:12.130 --> 09:14.506
Make a sound
I don't like...

09:18.339 --> 09:21.506
(water dripping, splashing)

09:24.130 --> 09:28.297
-(ropes straining)
-Fucking split this
island in two, you have.

09:34.297 --> 09:37.464
(heavy breathing)

09:39.631 --> 09:40.756
(thud)

09:41.381 --> 09:42.464
(grunts)

09:46.631 --> 09:49.714
Larry:
I don't give a shit
who your father was.

09:49.798 --> 09:51.339
(grunts)

09:51.422 --> 09:53.047
This ends now, boy.

09:54.923 --> 09:56.172
(thudding)

10:01.464 --> 10:03.089
(banging)

10:03.172 --> 10:05.881
(muffled groaning)

10:08.464 --> 10:10.714
♪

10:21.297 --> 10:22.506
(splash)

10:24.047 --> 10:26.464
(breathing faster)

10:29.506 --> 10:31.130
(rope straining)

10:34.047 --> 10:37.214
(heavy breathing)

10:38.547 --> 10:40.172
(gurgling)

10:47.297 --> 10:48.881
(heavy breathing)

10:50.130 --> 10:52.214
(banging)

10:55.631 --> 10:58.506
(heavy breathing)

11:00.714 --> 11:01.589
(grunting)

11:01.673 --> 11:02.673
(whimpers)

11:02.756 --> 11:05.923
(dramatic vocalizing)

11:08.172 --> 11:10.631
(rapid breathing)

11:10.714 --> 11:12.756
(vocalizing ends)

11:15.047 --> 11:17.214
(Larry breathing weakly)

11:23.756 --> 11:26.923
(banging, wood cracking)

11:28.255 --> 11:29.631
(clattering)

11:42.089 --> 11:45.756
(Larry breathing weakly)

11:52.673 --> 11:53.756
(grunts)

11:58.422 --> 12:01.381
(straining)

12:01.464 --> 12:04.589
(panting)

12:11.631 --> 12:13.130
(breathing weakly)

12:13.214 --> 12:16.464
♪

12:25.047 --> 12:27.255
(weak breathing continues)

12:34.297 --> 12:35.422
(snorts)

12:41.130 --> 12:42.214
(grunts)

12:54.214 --> 12:56.547
(grunting)

13:12.005 --> 13:15.130
♪

13:19.714 --> 13:21.839
(cutting rope)

13:31.047 --> 13:33.964
(tense, atonal music playing)

13:34.047 --> 13:37.673
(foliage crunching)

13:47.214 --> 13:49.381
(waves washing ashore)

13:59.172 --> 14:02.172
(sloshing)

14:02.255 --> 14:03.589
(grunts)

14:04.714 --> 14:05.798
(gasps)

14:06.506 --> 14:09.589
(grunting)

14:09.923 --> 14:11.381
Ah!

14:36.005 --> 14:37.381
(sighs)

14:39.255 --> 14:40.923
(scuttling)

14:42.297 --> 14:45.422
♪

14:47.673 --> 14:49.839
(birds chirping)

14:57.547 --> 15:00.839
(panting)

15:05.089 --> 15:07.964
(heavy breathing)

15:16.964 --> 15:18.339
(alarm beeping)

15:26.798 --> 15:30.005
(table scraping, rattling)

15:38.839 --> 15:42.422
(footsteps approaching)

15:42.506 --> 15:45.589
♪

15:45.673 --> 15:48.339
(heavy breathing)

15:53.506 --> 15:55.673
(panting)

15:58.964 --> 16:01.297
(seagulls cawing)

16:01.839 --> 16:05.214
(panting)

16:08.422 --> 16:11.589
(waves washing ashore)

16:24.714 --> 16:27.881
(splashing)

16:38.464 --> 16:41.422
(panting)

16:41.506 --> 16:44.673
(splashing)

16:46.881 --> 16:50.047
(grunting)

16:55.089 --> 16:58.005
♪

16:58.089 --> 17:00.255
(panting)

17:07.005 --> 17:09.089
(grunting)

17:10.631 --> 17:13.673
(wind blowing)

17:13.756 --> 17:16.798
♪

17:21.547 --> 17:23.255
(grunting)

17:31.297 --> 17:33.255
(gasping)

17:44.464 --> 17:45.798
(gasps)

17:50.047 --> 17:51.130
Ah!

17:55.130 --> 17:56.881
(tense music playing)

17:56.964 --> 17:58.464
♪

17:59.255 --> 18:00.172
(inaudible)

18:00.631 --> 18:01.589
(gasps)

18:06.464 --> 18:08.589
(gasping)

18:11.506 --> 18:12.714
Don't!

18:13.172 --> 18:14.297
(inaudible)

18:17.839 --> 18:18.964
No--

18:21.506 --> 18:23.673
(grunting, choking)

18:25.130 --> 18:27.297
(screaming, gurgling)

18:29.172 --> 18:30.214
Ah!

18:30.964 --> 18:33.255
Jess:
It's me! I got you!

18:33.339 --> 18:36.589
(both yelling)

18:36.673 --> 18:38.214
(Jess gasping)

18:38.964 --> 18:40.798
I got you! (gasps)

18:41.339 --> 18:44.422
(panting, gasping)

18:44.506 --> 18:47.839
-(wind blowing)
-(Jess faintly gasping)

18:49.839 --> 18:51.172
(Sam gasping)

18:56.964 --> 18:59.547
Larry...
he's trying to kill me...

18:59.631 --> 19:01.923
(panting)

19:02.005 --> 19:04.881
He had weights to sink my body.

19:08.005 --> 19:09.964
I need to get off this island.

19:10.047 --> 19:13.214
(waves washing ashore)

19:14.631 --> 19:16.130
Jess:
What is that?

19:16.214 --> 19:18.839
(panting)

19:21.714 --> 19:23.339
Where...

19:24.881 --> 19:27.839
-Where did you find that?
-Where do you think I found it?

19:27.923 --> 19:31.339
It was hidden under
the sink in our room, Sam.

19:32.047 --> 19:34.089
It's 40,000 pounds.

19:35.005 --> 19:37.839
This is the money
you said was stolen.

19:37.923 --> 19:39.839
-I didn't know--
-It's the money

19:39.923 --> 19:43.047
I watched you accuse
another man of taking!

19:43.130 --> 19:45.381
♪

19:47.798 --> 19:50.339
Is this an episode?

19:50.422 --> 19:53.923
Is that what you said?
Ep-ep-episodic psychosis?

19:56.714 --> 19:59.464
-No, no, no. It's-I-I--
-Would you even know if it was?

20:00.673 --> 20:03.589
I mean, people chasing you?

20:04.506 --> 20:06.798
What, trying to kill you?

20:06.881 --> 20:08.589
It-it-- No, it-- (sighs)

20:08.673 --> 20:10.005
It's not an episode.

20:10.089 --> 20:12.673
-It's not an episode!
-How do you know it's not?!

20:12.756 --> 20:14.923
(panting)

20:21.464 --> 20:23.255
Oh, Jesus Christ.

20:25.464 --> 20:28.089
(panting)

20:30.005 --> 20:32.339
I need you...

20:32.422 --> 20:34.798
to help me get off Osea.

20:36.214 --> 20:38.339
(birds chirping)

20:43.464 --> 20:45.089
(sighs)

20:50.297 --> 20:53.172
-Did you find her?
-I found her. She's coming.

20:53.255 --> 20:55.839
She wanted to tell
her husband first.

20:55.923 --> 20:58.005
-Why?
-To warn him about Larry.

20:59.172 --> 21:00.839
She seemed scared.

21:12.839 --> 21:15.172
I'm sorry you got
mixed up in all this.

21:20.172 --> 21:22.673
I just wanna get
home with my girls.

21:25.422 --> 21:27.047
That's all I want.

21:32.673 --> 21:33.839
(Sam sighs)

21:46.005 --> 21:47.089
(sighs)

21:48.339 --> 21:51.047
Jess:
What was he like?
Your son.

21:57.214 --> 21:59.381
He was a handful, actually.

22:05.255 --> 22:07.631
He had a bit of a problem
with right and wrong.

22:07.714 --> 22:11.547
♪

22:12.714 --> 22:14.881
I remember Cas was worried.

22:16.547 --> 22:18.547
'Cause he got into
a cruel phase,

22:18.631 --> 22:20.839
torturing insects and so on.

22:24.464 --> 22:28.422
He was just being a kid.
He could be so loving.

22:33.047 --> 22:34.214
Sam: Yeah.

22:37.798 --> 22:39.923
Yeah, he was tricky.

22:48.798 --> 22:51.798
I keep finding these
things all over the island.

22:51.881 --> 22:54.881
-Real ones, too.
-In some cultures,
crickets are a sign

22:54.964 --> 22:57.297
of rains and flooding.

22:58.714 --> 23:00.506
How can anybody
believe this stuff?

23:00.589 --> 23:03.673
Jess:
Doesn't matter how.
It's how much.

23:03.756 --> 23:06.339
I grew up in
a religious community.

23:06.422 --> 23:08.964
It was almost like a cult,

23:09.047 --> 23:12.381
and believe me, if our pastor
said the end was nigh,

23:12.464 --> 23:16.255
we started buying tin cans
and prepping our shelters.

23:16.339 --> 23:18.506
For them, it's not belief.

23:19.547 --> 23:22.089
It's immutable fucking fact.

23:22.172 --> 23:25.214
♪

23:25.297 --> 23:27.422
Oh, and...

23:28.673 --> 23:30.130
death.

23:32.130 --> 23:34.339
Crickets are also
a sign of death.

23:42.172 --> 23:45.339
(thunder rumbling)

23:47.756 --> 23:50.881
(indistinct chatter)

23:53.130 --> 23:55.130
Mr. Martin:
<i>Oh, flip.</i>

23:55.214 --> 23:56.881
Flippin' hell. This is bad.

23:56.964 --> 24:00.214
-This is really flippin' bad.
-Calm the fuck down, fucko.

24:00.297 --> 24:03.089
-Can you get us out of here?
-Mr. Martin: Yeah, of course.

24:03.172 --> 24:05.255
Of course we can.
We can, can't we, love?

24:05.339 --> 24:06.714
That's what I was
trying to do last night.

24:06.798 --> 24:09.964
-I was gonna lock
him in the chapel--
-Lock him in?

24:10.047 --> 24:12.381
Well, it's being
rewired. It's...

24:12.464 --> 24:14.130
a death trap.
No one will go inside.

24:14.214 --> 24:15.881
I was gonna hide him
in there until dawn--

24:15.964 --> 24:17.631
Jess:
What about a boat?
You said Tomo--

24:17.714 --> 24:19.547
Why does Larry
want me dead?

24:19.631 --> 24:20.673
Mr. Martin:
Sam,

24:20.756 --> 24:22.631
you were saying things
of the girl's father.

24:22.714 --> 24:24.631
-People don't take to that.
-No, no, it's not that.

24:24.714 --> 24:26.297
And you had
a closeness with her.

24:26.381 --> 24:29.964
-I'm not saying it was
impropriety. Not for one--
-It's not that.

24:30.047 --> 24:32.631
He wasn't angry.
He just wanted me gone.

24:32.714 --> 24:34.464
(rain pattering)

24:34.547 --> 24:36.714
That fucking ceremony...

24:38.714 --> 24:42.089
Preacher and the wine
and the meat.

24:42.172 --> 24:44.673
Mrs. Martin:
Tell him. Tell him everything.

24:51.547 --> 24:54.589
The man in the white suit,
the Father?

24:55.631 --> 24:57.923
Well, he can't die,
God bless him.

24:58.005 --> 25:00.214
Not till he's sure
he can pass it on.

25:01.047 --> 25:03.381
Osea needs a true father, Sam.

25:03.464 --> 25:06.005
Me. You're talking about me.

25:06.089 --> 25:08.214
♪

25:08.297 --> 25:10.547
Mr. Martin:
The day you lost your
boy on the mainland,

25:10.631 --> 25:12.881
you come to meet
someone, right?

25:14.089 --> 25:15.673
How do you know that?

25:15.756 --> 25:18.047
Mr. Martin:
It was him, the Father.

25:18.130 --> 25:21.130
Somehow, he found you.
He was gonna
tell you everything.

25:22.589 --> 25:25.172
We only found out that very day.
We didn't even know, did we?

25:25.255 --> 25:27.297
-People were furious.
-He's a fucking idiot.

25:27.381 --> 25:29.422
-Now, love...
-He's a fucking moron.

25:29.506 --> 25:31.005
He was never supposed
to sit in that role.

25:31.089 --> 25:33.756
Ever since he took over,
Osea's decayed.

25:35.255 --> 25:37.714
See, we'd searched for years.

25:37.798 --> 25:40.422
And there you suddenly
were that very day.

25:41.172 --> 25:42.589
And we panicked.

25:43.631 --> 25:45.506
But there you were,

25:45.589 --> 25:47.255
with your son.

25:51.422 --> 25:52.923
What about my son?

25:55.005 --> 25:56.964
Mr. Martin:
There were two ideas.

25:57.839 --> 26:00.547
One was to come,
talk to you,

26:00.631 --> 26:03.255
ask you to take
your rightful place.

26:03.339 --> 26:06.172
But how do you tell a grown
man something like that?

26:08.339 --> 26:10.381
So, there was a second idea...

26:10.464 --> 26:12.172
♪

26:12.255 --> 26:14.422
which was to take your boy.

26:16.798 --> 26:17.714
Take my son?

26:17.798 --> 26:19.839
Mr. Martin:
The wrong man was Father.

26:19.923 --> 26:22.756
We were in decline.
The world was in decline.

26:22.839 --> 26:26.130
Your son was a direct descendant
of Charrington himself!

26:28.005 --> 26:31.589
-(wood creaking)
-So, a person was spoken to
to see if, in theory,

26:31.673 --> 26:33.506
he could or would take your boy.

26:34.297 --> 26:35.714
He does it,

26:35.798 --> 26:38.506
and he gets a place
here for his family.

26:38.589 --> 26:41.255
-Imagine what that is
for those that believe.
-(scraping)

26:41.339 --> 26:44.130
-To live in the world's soul.
-(Sam gasps)

26:45.297 --> 26:47.547
The man we spoke to...

26:47.631 --> 26:49.756
well, he was confused.
He wasn't all there.

26:49.839 --> 26:52.130
-Who did you speak to?
-(wood creaking)

26:53.464 --> 26:55.673
-Mr. Martin: Goltan.
-(scraping)

26:56.673 --> 26:57.964
We spoke to Goltan.

26:58.756 --> 27:00.839
He was never meant
to hurt your boy.

27:00.923 --> 27:02.547
(scraping)

27:02.631 --> 27:04.631
-Whose idea--
-Mr. Martin:
He was just confused.

27:04.714 --> 27:06.047
He weren't supposed
to get violent.

27:06.130 --> 27:09.047
Whose idea was it
to take my son?

27:10.339 --> 27:13.255
♪

27:13.339 --> 27:16.130
-Mine.
-(wood scraping)

27:16.214 --> 27:18.381
And I've regretted it with
every single breath since.

27:18.464 --> 27:21.255
-Your idea. It was
your fucking idea?
-Is it now?

27:22.214 --> 27:24.923
Is now the time that
you're gonna give in

27:25.005 --> 27:26.798
to the rage inside you, Sam?

27:26.881 --> 27:29.547
(heavy breathing)

27:40.214 --> 27:42.381
I want you to listen to me.

27:44.255 --> 27:45.631
All of this,

27:45.714 --> 27:48.547
everything you believe in,
is fucking nonsense.

27:50.839 --> 27:53.631
It's magic and pixies,

27:53.714 --> 27:55.005
and fake gods.

27:55.089 --> 27:57.923
-It's not fake. Don't say fake.
-It cost my son his life.

27:58.005 --> 28:00.506
My son is dead
because of your fucking garbage.

28:00.589 --> 28:03.297
This shit that you believe in.

28:04.422 --> 28:06.089
I wanna get off this island.

28:08.464 --> 28:10.172
I would rather
slit my own throat

28:10.255 --> 28:13.297
than come back here
for one more minute.

28:15.172 --> 28:17.172
(breathing heavily)

28:17.255 --> 28:20.255
♪

28:34.381 --> 28:35.714
Okay.

28:37.631 --> 28:39.297
You're right. I'm sorry.

28:42.005 --> 28:44.255
Time to get you
off the island.

28:45.839 --> 28:47.673
Listen, love...

28:47.756 --> 28:50.172
Don't you think
he's lost enough?

28:52.339 --> 28:54.631
It's time we paid
for our sin.

29:01.047 --> 29:03.506
-(birds chirping)
-Mr. Martin: Sam,

29:03.589 --> 29:06.089
Osea is the world's
beating heart.

29:06.172 --> 29:08.798
-It needs its father.
-Where's Epona?

29:08.881 --> 29:11.381
Mrs. Martin:
We don't know. She's missin'.

29:11.464 --> 29:14.089
You think I'm leaving that
child alone here with you?

29:14.172 --> 29:17.089
Mrs. Martin:
We don't know where she is.
They're looking for her.

29:18.547 --> 29:20.422
We're gonna head east,
that's where Tomo is,

29:20.506 --> 29:22.381
-and we're gonna stay quiet.
-Mr. Martin: It's just that

29:22.464 --> 29:25.506
you walked in on Epona at
exactly the right moment.

29:25.589 --> 29:27.089
It means something,
Sam, it has to--

29:27.172 --> 29:30.130
Mrs. Martin:
Shut your fucking fuck
and move your fucking feet.

29:30.214 --> 29:32.339
(birds chirping)

29:33.673 --> 29:36.339
♪

29:36.422 --> 29:38.631
I was just speaking, that's all.

29:40.839 --> 29:43.005
I hope you know
what you're doing.

29:53.005 --> 29:55.172
(insect crunches)

30:06.172 --> 30:07.923
Man:
Spread out!

30:09.047 --> 30:10.881
Jess:
What are they doing?

30:11.673 --> 30:13.381
Mrs. Martin:
They're looking for him.

30:13.464 --> 30:15.881
All Osea is getting
dragged into this now.

30:18.673 --> 30:20.881
You two cross over,

30:20.964 --> 30:22.547
and then we'll follow.

30:25.631 --> 30:26.714
Alright.

30:31.422 --> 30:34.547
(wind blowing)

30:37.255 --> 30:39.714
-Come on then.
-Where?

30:40.881 --> 30:43.839
Well, that prick there,

30:43.923 --> 30:46.881
trust him with my life,
but not with this.

30:46.964 --> 30:50.089
♪

30:54.339 --> 30:57.464
(birds chirping)

31:06.547 --> 31:08.255
What is it?

31:10.255 --> 31:13.047
Those tunnels, do you--
do you see anything?

31:17.381 --> 31:19.047
Sam:
No, nothing.

31:19.130 --> 31:20.923
Mrs. Martin:
(sighs) Maybe not then.

31:21.005 --> 31:23.089
Maybe I'm just...

31:25.881 --> 31:28.089
Well, what if you're not?

31:30.547 --> 31:32.130
You stay here.

31:32.214 --> 31:34.339
I'll head up,
see if it's clear, and...

31:35.631 --> 31:38.005
if it is, then I'll come back
and we'll head on.

31:38.089 --> 31:40.005
If there are people there,
what about you?

31:40.089 --> 31:42.547
-I'll be fine.
-Will you?

31:42.631 --> 31:44.589
What, and you fucking will?

31:45.339 --> 31:47.673
Stay here.
Don't go anywhere, okay?

31:51.798 --> 31:54.839
♪

32:10.673 --> 32:13.839
(wind blowing)

32:21.381 --> 32:23.506
♪

32:27.881 --> 32:29.214
(sighs)

32:34.005 --> 32:37.172
(inaudible)

32:58.547 --> 33:00.172
(opens door)

33:04.381 --> 33:06.506
Hello?

33:24.297 --> 33:25.673
(sighs)

33:27.464 --> 33:30.923
♪

33:57.923 --> 34:00.923
(heavy breathing)

34:10.839 --> 34:12.255
(gasps)

34:23.672 --> 34:24.797
(drip)

34:26.505 --> 34:29.130
(squishing)

34:29.589 --> 34:30.964
(gasps)

34:39.964 --> 34:42.964
(dramatic music playing)

34:43.047 --> 34:45.547
(pained breathing)

34:45.630 --> 34:48.089
♪

34:48.172 --> 34:49.755
Oh!

34:49.839 --> 34:53.005
(pained breathing)

34:58.297 --> 35:00.506
Mrs. Martin:
Move away from that child.

35:03.255 --> 35:05.381
I said move, now.

35:06.506 --> 35:07.673
(Sam gasping)

35:10.714 --> 35:12.339
Sam:
It-- I...

35:13.005 --> 35:14.631
It wasn't me.

35:15.339 --> 35:18.255
I didn't-- I didn't do it.

35:18.339 --> 35:21.005
-Of course you didn't.
-(heavy breathing)

35:22.339 --> 35:23.964
She did.

35:25.381 --> 35:27.005
Sam:
What?

35:29.297 --> 35:32.547
She offered herself to
the gods in those woods.

35:34.214 --> 35:36.381
To heal our sin.

35:37.130 --> 35:39.839
Hanged herself to heal Osea.

35:41.547 --> 35:43.798
And the gods saw it,

35:43.881 --> 35:46.547
and they brought you to us.

35:49.756 --> 35:52.297
You didn't wanna stay.

35:52.381 --> 35:54.214
(Sam breathing heavily)

35:55.464 --> 35:57.714
I always knew
she was incredible, but...

35:59.714 --> 36:01.923
I never knew she
had this in her.

36:03.756 --> 36:06.422
The blade, the position...

36:09.047 --> 36:10.839
She must've lay
here alone all night,

36:10.923 --> 36:13.089
bleeding out under that sheet.

36:14.381 --> 36:15.923
(Sam gasps)

36:16.714 --> 36:18.756
It's ancient, this.

36:19.714 --> 36:23.089
She did it because
I wouldn't stay?

36:23.172 --> 36:25.923
Mrs. Martin:
She wanted you to
be Father, Sam.

36:28.255 --> 36:30.422
Just like they all do.

36:31.130 --> 36:33.297
-Like I did.
-Ah...

36:33.381 --> 36:36.673
But I know now, after
what you said back there,

36:36.756 --> 36:38.964
-it's not gonna be possible.
-(sighs)

36:43.047 --> 36:45.255
(exhales) Larry was right.

36:48.214 --> 36:50.881
You're not the answer.
You're the problem.

36:50.964 --> 36:53.214
And there can only be
one Father.

36:54.339 --> 36:55.798
Sam:
So, what?

36:56.714 --> 36:58.422
You're gonna kill me?

37:00.130 --> 37:02.589
And your holy fucking

37:02.673 --> 37:05.756
succession is restored.

37:05.839 --> 37:08.923
You get your oysters back,
and the world is healed,

37:09.005 --> 37:12.881
and that old man becomes
some sort of god?

37:12.964 --> 37:15.297
Mrs. Martin:
Him? Fuck no. He's useless.

37:16.005 --> 37:17.631
Who then?!

37:41.297 --> 37:42.756
Nathan.

37:42.839 --> 37:45.964
♪

37:47.339 --> 37:49.798
Is my son alive?

37:49.881 --> 37:52.172
Mrs. Martin:
You've seen him,
haven't you, Sam?

37:56.631 --> 37:59.839
You knew.
Come on, you knew.

38:01.047 --> 38:03.631
No, no, there was a body.
I-I-I--

38:03.714 --> 38:05.964
Mrs. Martin:
It was Epona's brother.

38:06.756 --> 38:08.381
Same age as your lad.

38:09.464 --> 38:11.673
Mimir saw to the paperwork.

38:14.464 --> 38:16.714
You can die happy, Sam.

38:16.798 --> 38:18.506
Your son's alive.

38:18.589 --> 38:20.130
Can I see him?

38:20.214 --> 38:22.422
Mrs. Martin:
No. It's too late for that.

38:23.923 --> 38:25.964
I need you to move
away from her.

38:26.047 --> 38:28.214
We mustn't sully what she did.

38:29.381 --> 38:31.756
-(blow lands)
-Move!

38:34.089 --> 38:36.297
Sam:
You didn't want
the others to know.

38:36.381 --> 38:39.089
They still think
you can lead us.

38:40.756 --> 38:42.964
Scared of what they'll do?

38:43.047 --> 38:45.047
My problem, not yours.

38:45.130 --> 38:48.381
♪

38:49.381 --> 38:50.923
Ah.

38:51.005 --> 38:52.089
(gun thuds)

38:53.881 --> 38:56.214
I wanna see him.

38:56.297 --> 38:58.547
Keep moving, Sam.

39:01.339 --> 39:03.381
I need to know more about him.

39:04.297 --> 39:05.923
He's fine.

39:06.005 --> 39:08.214
He's a good lad. He's happy.

39:12.422 --> 39:14.214
When things get better,

39:15.130 --> 39:17.297
the others will understand.

39:18.547 --> 39:20.089
And they'll forgive.

39:23.089 --> 39:26.005
If the soul of
the world is sick,

39:26.089 --> 39:28.255
then so is the world.

39:29.798 --> 39:31.839
I mean,

39:31.923 --> 39:34.089
Christ, just look at it.

39:36.089 --> 39:38.547
We on this island

39:38.631 --> 39:41.047
bear such responsibility.

39:43.047 --> 39:44.756
But we fucked up.

39:46.381 --> 39:49.255
What you and I do here today

39:49.339 --> 39:51.464
will help billions.

39:55.673 --> 39:57.172
I wanna see him.

39:59.422 --> 40:01.130
Keep moving, Sam.

40:01.881 --> 40:03.255
I wanna see him.

40:03.339 --> 40:05.506
-I said keep moving.
-I need to see him!

40:05.589 --> 40:08.214
(zap, explosion echoing)

40:08.297 --> 40:11.464
(high-pitched ringing)

40:12.464 --> 40:15.297
(zapping)

40:19.089 --> 40:21.673
(groaning)

40:23.089 --> 40:25.297
(zapping continues)

40:29.506 --> 40:31.714
♪

40:33.005 --> 40:34.339
(sighs)

40:37.756 --> 40:40.673
(scraping)

40:48.714 --> 40:50.339
(muffled groaning)

40:53.005 --> 40:54.631
(zapping)

40:57.214 --> 40:58.839
(muffled groan)

41:03.839 --> 41:06.547
(ringing continues)

41:10.214 --> 41:11.339
(gunshot)

41:12.673 --> 41:13.589
(thud)

41:16.422 --> 41:17.381
(muffled click)

41:17.464 --> 41:20.589
(wind blowing)

41:26.589 --> 41:27.714
(thud)

41:35.506 --> 41:38.422
(ringing)

41:38.506 --> 41:41.673
(muffled breathing)

41:45.756 --> 41:48.881
♪

41:51.839 --> 41:54.964
(ringing continues)

41:56.589 --> 41:59.464
(muffled panting)

42:03.673 --> 42:06.255
(muffled snapping)

42:10.130 --> 42:12.297
(muffled ringtone playing)

42:20.005 --> 42:22.631
(muffled ringtone)

42:24.005 --> 42:26.172
(muffled):
Fuck, fuck!

42:26.255 --> 42:28.589
(ringing)

42:29.631 --> 42:32.130
Aday? Aday!

42:32.214 --> 42:33.798
Oh, my God!

42:34.673 --> 42:36.839
Yeah, I know! I'm here!

42:37.381 --> 42:38.673
Please help me!

42:40.714 --> 42:43.923
<i>I'm on an island.</i>
<i>Osea Island...</i>

42:44.422 --> 42:45.631
<i>Aday!</i>

42:46.631 --> 42:48.798
(weakly):
Hello?

42:48.881 --> 42:50.673
-Aday?
-(line disconnects)

42:50.756 --> 42:52.714
-(beeping)
-Ah!

42:52.798 --> 42:55.964
♪

42:57.130 --> 42:58.047
Ah!

42:58.130 --> 43:00.297
(wind blowing)

43:01.631 --> 43:03.923
(wings flapping)

43:12.005 --> 43:13.673
(buzzing)

43:16.673 --> 43:19.798
(rain falling)

43:24.589 --> 43:25.673
My phone!

43:36.506 --> 43:39.506
(panting)

43:43.923 --> 43:45.339
-(cracking)
-(gasps)

43:47.464 --> 43:50.047
(panting)

43:53.714 --> 43:56.881
♪

44:10.923 --> 44:12.714
(muffled grunt)

44:14.923 --> 44:16.047
(coughs)

44:17.047 --> 44:19.005
(grunting)

44:19.673 --> 44:21.881
(muffled coughing)

44:21.964 --> 44:24.589
(thunder rumbling)

44:26.130 --> 44:28.714
(panting)

44:32.756 --> 44:35.881
(rain gets louder)

44:37.839 --> 44:40.714
(thunder rumbling)

44:40.798 --> 44:44.047
-(ears ringing)
-(muffled rain)

44:45.172 --> 44:46.798
(muffled panting)

44:48.589 --> 44:49.923
(twig snaps)

44:53.839 --> 44:55.673
(muffled):
Don't come near me.
I will kill you.

44:55.756 --> 44:58.339
I will fucking kill you!

44:58.422 --> 45:01.464
♪

45:13.130 --> 45:15.297
He's in there,
isn't he?

45:16.381 --> 45:18.005
I'm taking the boy
with me. I'm not--

45:18.089 --> 45:20.172
I'm not leaving without him.

45:20.255 --> 45:22.464
(muffled):
Tomo's boat is out waitin'.

45:23.756 --> 45:25.881
Take it to the mainland.

45:25.964 --> 45:27.381
Call the police.

45:27.464 --> 45:30.130
(ringing continues)

45:30.214 --> 45:32.547
Can't leave him here on his own.

45:32.631 --> 45:34.881
Jason:
He won't be on his own.

45:34.964 --> 45:37.130
He'll be with me.

45:38.422 --> 45:40.589
Get the police. Now.

45:42.964 --> 45:45.964
(warbled vocalizing)

45:46.047 --> 45:49.130
(panting)

45:50.923 --> 45:54.673
(vocalizing continues)

45:54.756 --> 45:57.339
-(muffled): Oh God!
-(muffled): Sam, it's me!

45:57.422 --> 46:00.005
-(ringing continues)
-Oh Jess...

46:00.089 --> 46:01.673
Oh my God!

46:03.005 --> 46:04.673
What happened?

46:06.005 --> 46:07.673
I can't hear...

46:09.923 --> 46:12.130
Mr. Martin,
where is he?

46:12.214 --> 46:15.464
He spoke to Tomo,
and then he heard a shot.

46:15.547 --> 46:17.172
He told me to wait here.

46:17.255 --> 46:19.255
Where's the boat?

46:19.339 --> 46:21.214
We need to go.

46:22.047 --> 46:24.172
♪

46:28.631 --> 46:30.130
Tomo:
Where are the Martins?

46:30.214 --> 46:32.255
They had to go back!

46:32.339 --> 46:33.839
There was a shot fired!

46:33.923 --> 46:36.714
-Tomo: They should be here!
-Jess: They...

46:36.798 --> 46:38.839
They said you'd take us!

46:40.589 --> 46:43.547
-They should be here.
-They're waiting!

46:43.631 --> 46:46.547
Around the corner!
They said you'd know!

46:46.631 --> 46:48.923
Around the...
the rocks!

46:49.005 --> 46:51.172
He means the headland!

46:51.255 --> 46:53.005
Tomo:
I know what he means.

46:57.422 --> 46:59.547
(splashing)

47:00.714 --> 47:02.881
(Jess and Sam grunting)

47:06.839 --> 47:08.923
(panting)

47:11.172 --> 47:12.798
Tomo:
The tide's low.

47:12.881 --> 47:15.381
Shortest way is west.
If it's too shallow for that,

47:15.464 --> 47:18.172
we'll go north and circle round.

47:18.255 --> 47:22.339
-There's channels to
the mainland there.
-(Jess panting)

47:22.422 --> 47:26.464
We have to be careful once we
get pushed back on the flats.

47:26.547 --> 47:28.881
Sam:
Jess, can you drive the boat?

47:28.964 --> 47:31.255
-Jess: What are you doing, Sam?
-Can you drive
this fucking boat?!

47:31.339 --> 47:33.381
I think so, yeah!

47:33.464 --> 47:35.839
-You, off.
-Sam, he's with us!

47:35.923 --> 47:39.422
He's not! No!
None of them are with us!
Get off.

47:39.506 --> 47:41.172
♪

47:41.255 --> 47:43.422
-Get off the boat!
-Hey...

47:44.798 --> 47:46.422
You belong here, Sam...

47:50.047 --> 47:51.422
Stay...

47:52.422 --> 47:55.130
-Or the darkness inside you--
-Get off!

47:55.756 --> 47:57.047
Go! Go!

47:58.005 --> 48:00.255
-Tomo: Sam!
-(engine revving)

48:00.798 --> 48:02.422
Sam!

48:04.839 --> 48:06.464
(engine revving)

48:10.047 --> 48:12.673
Jess:
Not good at this.

48:12.756 --> 48:14.964
There are mudflats
everywhere.

48:16.005 --> 48:19.172
I think we need to go by
the pier and then head out,

48:19.255 --> 48:20.964
through the channels, he said.

48:24.297 --> 48:25.923
You okay?

48:27.297 --> 48:30.547
-My son's here.
-Jess: What?

48:30.631 --> 48:32.547
He's alive
and he's on this island.

48:32.631 --> 48:34.714
He's in that house,
that big house.

48:34.798 --> 48:37.172
Jess:
What do you mean?
Goltan didn't...?

48:38.130 --> 48:40.464
They kept him, Jess.
They kept him here.

48:41.631 --> 48:44.756
♪

48:55.047 --> 48:58.214
-(indistinct chatter)
-Jess: Shit. The tide's pulling!

48:58.297 --> 49:00.381
-What?
-I think it's okay.

49:00.464 --> 49:03.047
-It's just bringing us close.
-There's people over there.

49:04.798 --> 49:08.047
(indistinct chatter)

49:14.339 --> 49:16.506
Sam:
What are they doing?

49:21.964 --> 49:24.130
What's happening?

49:25.047 --> 49:27.964
-(thud)
-(grunts) No...

49:28.047 --> 49:29.547
We're getting
caught on the flats!

49:29.631 --> 49:31.756
(engine revving)

49:37.756 --> 49:39.714
I'm pulling full throttle!

49:40.255 --> 49:41.381
(straining)

49:45.297 --> 49:47.422
(Sam straining)

49:54.547 --> 49:57.214
(straining) That's it!

49:58.339 --> 49:59.798
Go! Go!

49:59.881 --> 50:02.506
(engine idles)

50:09.714 --> 50:11.798
Jess...

50:14.381 --> 50:16.130
The place I'm from...

50:16.923 --> 50:19.089
it's like this.

50:20.589 --> 50:24.339
My husband, he knows
the people here
and they're watching me.

50:24.422 --> 50:27.464
♪

50:30.297 --> 50:31.964
I need to leave.

50:32.798 --> 50:34.422
Please.

50:36.923 --> 50:39.172
My girls are...

50:39.255 --> 50:41.422
all that matter to me,
and you know that.

50:41.506 --> 50:43.714
I told you that, remember?

50:45.172 --> 50:46.547
(sighs)

50:48.339 --> 50:50.339
Jess, please--

50:50.422 --> 50:52.130
Jess:
Sit.

50:53.255 --> 50:55.214
Sit now.

50:55.297 --> 50:57.089
♪

50:57.172 --> 50:59.589
(women vocalizing)

51:00.172 --> 51:01.381
(sighs)

51:10.381 --> 51:13.464
♪

51:16.756 --> 51:19.422
(insects buzzing)

51:25.881 --> 51:28.964
♪

51:30.214 --> 51:33.381
(pier rattling)

51:50.130 --> 51:51.381
(indistinct chatter)

51:58.756 --> 52:01.881
(pier rattling)

52:16.422 --> 52:20.089
Mr. Martin:
This island's been divided about
what to do ever since you came.

52:21.881 --> 52:24.673
Ever since we knew of
your existence, in fact.

52:24.756 --> 52:26.923
It's quite thrown us. But...

52:27.839 --> 52:30.047
we're all in agreement now.

52:32.673 --> 52:33.756
(sighs)

52:35.547 --> 52:37.756
Father:

52:43.881 --> 52:46.005
The dark is here.

53:00.964 --> 53:02.381
(exhales sharply)

53:03.756 --> 53:07.047
-Father: Thank you.
-(inhales shakily)

53:09.422 --> 53:10.756
Thank you.

53:12.422 --> 53:14.130
(gasps)

53:14.714 --> 53:17.881
(cheering, applause)

53:19.089 --> 53:21.005
(panting)

53:21.089 --> 53:22.923
Mr. Martin:
Are you ready, Sam?

53:23.756 --> 53:26.089
Sam?

53:26.172 --> 53:28.506
Are you ready for
what happens next?

53:28.589 --> 53:31.589
(dramatic strings play)

53:31.673 --> 53:35.464
♪

53:40.214 --> 53:41.381
(sighs)

53:41.464 --> 53:43.631
(woman vocalizing)

53:48.547 --> 53:50.130
(sobs)

53:58.631 --> 54:00.255
(Sam sobs)

54:06.047 --> 54:09.172
(breathing heavily)

54:24.005 --> 54:26.631
(crying)

54:38.172 --> 54:41.214
♪

54:48.631 --> 54:51.714
(panting)

55:10.255 --> 55:12.631
(crying)

55:12.714 --> 55:14.881
(strings, vocalizing intensify)

55:26.673 --> 55:28.756
(sobbing)

55:47.422 --> 55:50.547
(music softens)

56:01.422 --> 56:02.756
(crickets chirping)

56:04.005 --> 56:05.506
(buzzing)

56:05.589 --> 56:08.631
♪

56:26.172 --> 56:29.214
(buzzing intensifies)

56:29.297 --> 56:32.422
♪

56:38.756 --> 56:41.923
(buzzing intensifies)

56:51.798 --> 56:55.005
(light strings playing,
woman vocalizing)

57:20.422 --> 57:23.506
♪

58:15.506 --> 58:17.381
JESS: <i>The ancient Celts believed</i>

58:17.464 --> 58:20.839
<i>that Osea was the soul</i>
<i>of the world.</i>

58:21.589 --> 58:23.214
<i>If Osea's sick,</i>

58:23.506 --> 58:25.547
<i>the whole planet's sick.</i>

58:25.923 --> 58:27.923
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

58:29.047 --> 58:31.673
We are gonna have ourselves
an adventure, right?

58:31.756 --> 58:33.047
Just us three.

58:34.547 --> 58:36.756
HELEN:
<i>This holiday's like a new start.</i>

58:37.255 --> 58:38.839
MAN: <i>This place,</i>

58:39.422 --> 58:41.255
<i>why's it so important to you?</i>

58:41.964 --> 58:43.756
HELEN: <i>My girls</i>
<i>have been through a lot.</i>

58:44.005 --> 58:45.589
I want them to feel good.

58:46.589 --> 58:47.881
(WHISPERS) Then leave.

58:48.089 --> 58:50.214
♪ (MUSIC CONTINUES) ♪

58:50.464 --> 58:51.881
HELEN: <i>What's going on?</i>

58:52.631 --> 58:54.839
MR. MARTIN: <i>You're in</i>
<i>exactly the right place,</i>

58:54.923 --> 58:56.589
and at exactly the right time.

58:56.923 --> 58:59.756
Everyone here's acting
like something bad's
gonna happen.

59:00.297 --> 59:01.589
Mom?

59:03.923 --> 59:05.923
MRS. MARTIN:
<i>We've had our customs for years.</i>

59:07.297 --> 59:09.089
I'm not apologizing for 'em.

59:11.339 --> 59:13.130
Things are out of balance.

59:14.464 --> 59:16.089
I need your help, Ellie.

59:16.172 --> 59:18.631
♪ (MUSIC INTENSIFIES) ♪

59:19.047 --> 59:20.547
HELEN: <i>We need to leave</i>
<i>this place.</i>

59:20.631 --> 59:21.881
(CLOCK CHIMES)

59:21.964 --> 59:23.881
Osea impacts the whole world.

59:24.547 --> 59:26.506
JESS:
<i>Things are going</i>
<i>to be different now.</i>

59:26.839 --> 59:28.089
(YELLING INDISTINCTLY)

59:28.172 --> 59:29.297
(CLOCK CHIMES)

59:29.756 --> 59:31.089
HELEN: <i>What have we done?</i>

59:31.297 --> 59:33.130
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪
